com.saasovation.common.port.adapter.messaging.rabbitmq

Class MessageConsumer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.saasovation.common.port.adapter.messaging.rabbitmq.MessageConsumer

  • public class MessageConsumer
extends java.lang.Object
    I am a message consumer, which facilitates receiving messages from a Queue. A MessageListener or a client may close me, terminating message consumption.

      • receiveOnly

        public void receiveOnly(java.lang.String[] aMessageTypes,
                        MessageListener aMessageListener)
        Receives only messages of types included in aMessageTypes on a separate thread and dispatches them to aMessageListener until I am closed or until the broker is shut down. The type must be included in the message's basic properties. If the message's type is null, the message is filtered out.
        Parameters:
        aMessageTypes - the String[] indicating filtered message types
        aMessageListener - the MessageListener that handles messages
